iced that the StAXResult class isn’t final and doesn't have a default constructor. I’ll have to think about public constructors for custom classes and naming conventions for tests!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying Java class structure**\\n\\nI'm diving into the details of creating a final class named `CustomStAXResult` that extends `StAXResult`. It needs to be a package-private top-level class, but I'm considering making its constructor public. I'm thinking about how `Class#getConstructor` behaves with public versus non-public classes, and whether a public constructor in a non-public class would even be accessible. If that’s the case, I need to ensure my helper class is public for proper instantiation. \\n\\nI should also consider using built-in subclasses like `javax.xml.transform.stax.StAXResult` for simplicity, and ensure my code adheres to formatting requirements, like avoiding wildcards and using `StandardCharsets`.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering SQLXML creation**\\n\\nI need to create a writable `SQLXML`, but I'm realizing that I can't use `JDBCSQLXML` directly. Instead, I could use the method `dataSource().getConnection().createSQLXML()` to get the `SQLXML`. I should think about writing a helper method named `newWritableSqlXml()` that would return an `SQLXML` and would need to handle closing the connection properly. Wait, can I even close the connection before using the `SQLXML`? It seems like I need to ensure I manage the connection correctly, since `createSQLXML()` returns a new instance without a reference to the connection.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test organization**\\n\\nI'm thinking I could combine the results into four tests, using assertions for clarity. However, I need to make sure that all top-level test classes are defined as public. It seems like I might actually need to set the new class to public as well. It’s important to keep the structure organized for proper testing and functionality, so I'll double-check that everything aligns with best practices.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_stP60slcXguppqhstLIto1ZC|fc_05680276128df6c50169f9812665ec819d863f18f9eb6710ac", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.hsqldb/hsqldb/2.4.1/src/test/java/org_hsqldb/hsqldb/JDBCSQLXMLTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_hsqldb.hsqldb;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.io.OutputStream;\nimport java.io.StringReader;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\nimport java.sql.Connection;\nimport java.sql.SQLXML;\n\nimport javax.xml.stream.XMLStreamWriter;\nimport javax.xml.transform.dom.DOMResult;\nimport javax.xml.transform.dom.DOMSource;\nimport javax.xml.transform.sax.SAXResult;\nimport javax.xml.transform.sax.SAXSource;\nimport javax.xml.transform.stax.StAXResult;\nimport javax.xml.transform.stax.StAXSource;\nimport javax.xml.transform.stream.StreamResult;\nimport javax.xml.transform.stream.StreamSource;\n\nimport org.hsqldb.jdbc.JDBCDataSource;\nimport org.hsqldb.jdbc.JDBCSQLXML;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.w3c.dom.Document;\nimport org.xml.sax.ContentHandler;\nimport org.xml.sax.helpers.AttributesImpl;\n\npublic class JDBCSQLXMLTest {\n    private static final String XML = \"<?xml version=\\\"1.0\\\" encoding=\\\"UTF-8\\\"?><root><child>value</child></root>\";\n\n    @Test\n    void createsStreamSourceWithRequestedSourceClass() throws Exception {\n        JDBCSQLXML sqlxml = newReadableSqlXml();\n\n        try {\n            StreamSource source = sqlxml.getSource(StreamSource.class);\n\n            assertThat(source.getReader()).isNotNull();\n        } finally {\n            sqlxml.free();\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void createsDomSourceWithRequestedSourceClass() throws Exception {\n        JDBCSQLXML sqlxml = newReadableSqlXml();\n\n        try {\n            DOMSource source = sqlxml.getSource(DOMSource.class);\n\n            assertThat(source.getNode()).isInstanceOf(Document.class);\n        } finally {\n            sqlxml.free();\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void createsSaxSourceWithRequestedSourceClass() throws Exception {\n        JDBCSQLXML sqlxml = newReadableSqlXml();\n\n        try {\n            SAXSource source = sqlxml.getSource(SAXSource.class);\n\n            assertThat(source.getInputSource()).isNotNull();\n            assertThat(source.getInputSource().getCharacterStream()).isNotNull();\n        } finally {\n            sqlxml.free();\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void createsStaxSourceWithRequestedSourceClass() throws Exception {\n        JDBCSQLXML sqlxml = newReadableSqlXml();\n\n        try {\n            StAXSource source = sqlxml.getSource(StAXSource.class);\n\n            assertThat(source.getXMLEventReader()).isNotNull();\n        } finally {\n            sqlxml.free();\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void createsStreamResultWithRequestedResultClass() throws Exception {\n        withWritableSqlXml(sqlxml -> {\n            StreamResult result = sqlxml.setResult(StreamResult.class);\n\n            try (OutputStream outputStream = result.getOutputStream()) {\n                outputStream.write(XML.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8));\n            }\n\n            assertThat(result.getOutputStream()).isNotNull();\n        });\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void createsDomResultWithRequestedResultClass() throws Exception {\n        withWritableSqlXml(sqlxml -> {\n            DOMResult result = sqlxml.setResult(DOMResult.class);\n\n            assertThat(result).isNotNull();\n        });\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void createsSaxResultWithRequestedResultClass() throws Exception {\n        withWritableSqlXml(sqlxml -> {\n            SAXResult result = sqlxml.setResult(SAXResult.class);\n            ContentHandler handler = result.getHandler();\n\n            handler.startDocument();\n            handler.startElement(\"\", \"root\", \"root\", new AttributesImpl());\n            handler.characters(\"value\".toCharArray(), 0, \"value\".length());\n            handler.endElement(\"\", \"root\", \"root\");\n            handler.endDocument();\n\n            assertThat(handler).isNotNull();\n        });\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void createsStaxResultWithRequestedResultClass() throws Exception {\n        withWritableSqlXml(sqlxml -> {\n            CustomStAXResult result = sqlxml.setResult(CustomStAXResult.class);\n            XMLStreamWriter writer = result.getXMLStreamWriter();\n\n            writer.writeStartDocument();\n            writer.writeStartElement(\"root\");\n            writer.writeCharacters(\"value\");\n            writer.writeEndElement();\n            writer.writeEndDocument();\n            writer.close();\n\n            assertThat(writer).isNotNull();\n        });\n    }\n\n    private static JDBCSQLXML newReadableSqlXml() throws Exception {\n        return new JDBCSQLXML(new StreamSource(new StringReader(XML)));\n    }\n\n    private static void withWritableSqlXml(SqlXmlConsumer consumer) throws Exception {\n        JDBCDataSource dataSource = new JDBCDataSource();\n\n        dataSource.setUrl(\"jdbc:hsqldb:mem:sqlxmlcoverage;shutdown=true\");\n        dataSource.setUser(\"SA\");\n        dataSource.setPassword(\"\");\n\n        try (Connection connection = dataSource.getConnection()) {\n            SQLXML sqlxml = connection.createSQLXML();\n\n            try {\n                consumer.accept(sqlxml);\n            } finally {\n                sqlxml.free();\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    @FunctionalInterface\n    private interface SqlXmlConsumer {\n        void accept(SQLXML sqlxml) throws Exception;\n    }\n\n    public static final class CustomStAXResult extends StAXResult {\n        public CustomStAXResult(XMLStreamWriter wr